      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Sheen_Header_v01.jpg\" width=\"1407\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542220045/Sheen_Header_v01.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330557789&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1407&amp;height=791\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542220045/Sheen_Header_v01.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330557789&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"1080\" data-width=\"1920\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542220081\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Sheen_Header_v01.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542220045\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"3f9657df-44aa-4532-af65-c23e253d40ac\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542220045/Sheen_Header_v01.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330557789&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1920&amp;height=1080 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542220045/Sheen_Header_v01.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330557789&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1407&amp;height=791 1x\"></span><p>Sheen is a useful view-dependent effect similar to a Fresnel effect in specular lobes of many materials.<br/><br/>Note that it is visible along the edges of objects as a reflective or shiny result. This is useful for creating looks like velvet or lustrous effects on stones and shiny fabrics.  You may find this similar to using Edge Color <em>alone</em> in PxrSurface Specular effects.</p><p><br/></p><h3 id=\"LamaSheen-SheenParameters\">Sheen Parameters</h3><p><strong>Color</strong></p><p>This provides the resulting color of the effect either through a flat color, texture connection, or a procedural texture.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>Roughness</strong></p><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">A greater value produces rougher or wider results that spread across the surface from the edge. At 1.0 it resembles a nearly diffuse surface and at 0.0 it's so thin it may be hard to see depending on the shape of your surface. Most objects will be realistic somewhere in between these values. Texturing this value may give you interesting effects like smudges, greasy fingerprints, and worn surfaces.</span></p><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table data-table-width=\"1800\" data-layout=\"align-start\" data-local-id=\"ee4994fb-3dc2-4c8b-ac75-14a0c69417e7\" class=\"confluenceTable\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"confluenceTd\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Sheen_roughness.0001.jpg\" width=\"217\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542220045/Sheen_roughness.0001.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330557789&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=217&amp;height=217\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542220045/Sheen_roughness.0001.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330557789&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"800\" data-width=\"800\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542220078\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Sheen_roughness.0001.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542220045\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"d96f12c8-b74f-412d-b212-7ba8a86f38